# nanite-plugin-{{ .inputs.plugin_name }}

{{ .inputs.description }}

Subprocess plugin for [Nanite](https://github.com/hollis-labs/nanite), built
on [`github.com/hollis-labs/plugin-sdk`]({{ .inputs.sdk_version }}).

## Install

During development, point the host at a local checkout:

```sh
nanite plugin install ./nanite-plugin-{{ .inputs.plugin_name }}
```

Released archives are published to the [Nanite plugin catalog](https://plugins.nanite.hollislabs.dev)
and install by id:

```sh
nanite plugin install {{ .inputs.plugin_name }}
```

## Capabilities

This plugin implements:

- `subprocess.Plugin` — `Init` / `Load` / `Unload`
{{- if .inputs.handler_command }}
- `subprocess.CommandHandler` — handles `/{{ .inputs.plugin_name }}` slash command
{{- end }}
{{- if .inputs.handler_event }}
- `subprocess.EventHandler` — subscribes to `message.sent` host events
{{- end }}
{{- if .inputs.handler_mcp }}
- `subprocess.MCPHandler` — serves MCP tools registered in `plugin.yaml`
{{- end }}
{{- if .inputs.handler_http }}
- `subprocess.HTTPHandler` — handles HTTP routes registered in `plugin.yaml`
{{- end }}

## Build

```sh
make build         # native binary at ./{{ .inputs.plugin_name }}
make test          # go test ./...
make vet           # go vet ./...
{{- if .inputs.include_ui }}
make build-ui      # vite-build the UI bundle into ui/dist/
{{- end }}
make release       # cross-compile + assemble per-platform archives in dist/archives/
```

## Release signing

`make release` signs each archive when `{{ .computed.signing_key_env }}` is set
to a base64-encoded Ed25519 private key. Generate a development keypair once:

```sh
make keygen
```

This writes `dev-signing-key.pub` (commit it) and prints the matching private
key — capture it in a password manager and export as `{{ .computed.signing_key_env }}`
when invoking `make release`.

